data.content:
Yes — MSTest v3+ supports `DynamicData` with **ValueTuples** instead of `object[]`, giving you compile-time type safety:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Key changes:**
- Return type: `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` instead of `IEnumerable<object[]>`
- Data uses tuple syntax `(...)` instead of array syntax `[...]`

This eliminates boxing and catches type mismatches at compile time. Requires **MSTest 3.3+**.
